The paper is about multiagent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of mean field theory and games also suggests a connection to game theory (cs.GT). The paper specifically focuses on multiagent systems (cs.MA) and introduces new algorithms for learning the types of agents, which involves some level of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the experiments conducted involve simulations of agents interacting in an environment, which could be considered a control or systems engineering problem (cs.SY).
